March 28, 2017

Do You Actually Need a Visualization?

The forum in which you’re presenting matters! If you are writing for a scientific journal, it will be a lot different than presenting in person to a thousand person audience. For example, what you see at a Ted Talk is very different than what you see when reading the Journal of Physics.

Point being: consider your audience!

First off, let’s talk about a high-level presentation. Everyone has seen a slideshow presented with fancy charts that add zero value. Do not be the person presenting something that way! Providing useless content will confuse the audience or lead to boredom.

If your point is to show YoY change of a single metric - show it as a simple number on the page in big bold font rather than a chart.

In this made up example, the author (me) is displaying revenue over the last few years (note: be more specific when it comes to what type of revenue you’re talking about)
